{
  "stem": "6257.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then my-- it must have been my grandfather and my uncle.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They built a-- it was a bunker, a hiding place, in the cellars, underneath a block of flats.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Where there was a kind of secret hole through which we-- and we began to-- as soon as we could hear the Germans and the Ukrainians, and whoever they were, Latvians, and the Jewish police sometimes were coming, we would run to the cellar and block ourselves in.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we could hear the shooting outside and shouting, that whoever was found who didn't come out, would be shot.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And so on.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But we were not found.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So yes, by that time it was certainly not a normal life.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We were-- and we somehow knew very quickly that it was-- that-- that people were being killed, and that they were being gassed.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Because I remember being-- he said, oh, don't worry about taking parcels of clothes or anything.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "In fact, I-- I was surprised after the war to discover that there were camps.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I thought everyone was being killed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think my mother must have said.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think that the people-- that it was normal.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That there was-- first of all, they were-- I heard about even before this happened in Warsaw, that in small towns, Jews were headed together and shot and gassed in some vans.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And later on when it happened, mostly there were people running-- running away from Treblinka even.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They would escape somehow and come back.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because there was nowhere for them to go, or come back to the ghetto and talk about it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I remember, one of the killer time's men talking about it, who had been in Treblinka, And-- and came back.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
